BlackHouse Media Group (BHMG) has emerged as the most decorated Nigerian firm at the SABRE Awards EMEA. BHM was nominated for four campaigns, putting the integrated communications company as the first among other agencies who were nominated. The company was also announced as a finalist in the Africa Consultancy of the Year category, making BHM the only Nigerian agency to be nominated for the award. This is the second year that BHM will be nominated alongside global heavyweights like BCW (WPP), Clockwork and Edelman.   IMG grows net profit by 27% to N372m     Heifer votes $3.5m for tractors     Customs Strike Force rakes in N8b in two months   Yearly, the world’s largest international competition in the field of public relations, SABRE Awards, puts a spotlight on the industry’s most outstanding achievements in branding and reputation management, focusing on programmes and initiatives that drive practical business impact. This year’s  will decorate winners at the Guildhall, London, on May 27. BHMG’s recognition of excellence were in the categories of ‘Capital Markets Communications’, ‘Corporate Social Responsibility’, ‘Crisis Management’ and ‘Africa’. The four nominations were MTN Public Offer, Coca-Cola World Without Waste, Project SafeUp and the issues management work for MTN. Some of the other nominees are Chain Reactions Nigeria, and Redrick Public Relations Limited. Commenting on the nominations, Founder and CEO, Ayeni Adekunle, says the recognition is “a welcome testament to BHM’s passion for the public relations profession, our people, clients, and the innovation that we believe will lead us into a great future.” Founded in Lagos in 2006, BlackHouse Media (BHM) is Nigeria’s leading public relations and reputation management company, providing services in strategic corporate communications, consumer and events PR, crisis communications, research & intelligence, content development, as well as government and media relations.